&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
{{&lt; /example &gt;}}</p>
<h2>Horizontal &amp; vertical gutters</h2>
<p><code>.g-*</code> classes can be used to control the horizontal gutter widths, for the following example we use a smaller gutter width, so there won't be a need to add the <code>.overflow-hidden</code> wrapper class.</p>
<p>{{&lt; example &gt;}}
&lt;div class=&quot;container text-center&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;row g-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;col-6&quot;&gt;
