<h2>No gutters</h2>
<p>The gutters between columns in our predefined grid classes can be removed with <code>.g-0</code>. This removes the negative <code>margin</code>s from <code>.row</code> and the horizontal <code>padding</code> from all immediate children columns.</p>
<p><strong>Need an edge-to-edge design?</strong> Drop the parent <code>.container</code> or <code>.container-fluid</code> and add <code>.mx-0</code> to the <code>.row</code> to prevent overflow.</p>
<p>In practice, here's how it looks. Note you can continue to use this with all other predefined grid classes (including column widths, responsive tiers, reorders, and more).</p>
<p>{{&lt; example class=&quot;bd-example-row&quot; &gt;}}
&lt;div class=&quot;row g-0 text-center&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;col-sm-6 col-md-8&quot;&gt;.col-sm-6 .col-md-8&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;col-6 col-md-4&quot;&gt;.col-6 .col-md-4&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
{{&lt; /example &gt;}}</p>
<h2>Change the gutters</h2>
<p>Classes are built from the <code>$gutters</code> Sass map which is inherited from the <code>$spacers</code> Sass map.</p>
<pre><code class="hljs scss"><span class="hljs-variable">$grid-gutter-width</span>: <span class="hljs-number">1.5rem</span>;
<span class="hljs-variable">$gutters</span>: (
  <span class="hljs-number">0</span>: <span class="hljs-number">0</span>,
  <span class="hljs-number">1</span>: <span class="hljs-variable">$spacer</span> * .<span class="hljs-number">25</span>,
  <span class="hljs-number">2</span>: <span class="hljs-variable">$spacer</span> * .<span class="hljs-number">5</span>,
  <span class="hljs-number">3</span>: <span class="hljs-variable">$spacer</span>,
  <span class="hljs-number">4</span>: <span class="hljs-variable">$spacer</span> * <span class="hljs-number">1.5</span>,
  <span class="hljs-number">5</span>: <span class="hljs-variable">$spacer</span> * <span class="hljs-number">3</span>,
);
</code></pre>

